Axonius, Inc. (Remote, reporting to headquarters in New York, NY) is seeking a DevOps Tech Lead. This role involves defining and creating complex technological solutions to address issues raised by the entire company in order to enhance Axonius' proprietary platform. 
 Specifically, the DevOps Tech Lead is responsible for designing and implementing Axonius' complex and unique tools and solutions in the following areas: 

 Leads the design of the company’s cloud infrastructure architecture, from the organizational account structure to the deployment of individual workloads. Defines where and how services run, and how they integrate with dependent systems across the platform. Establishes scalable, secure, and resilient infrastructure patterns; 
 Leads the design and configuration of the networking architecture supporting distributed services across the Axonius platform. Defines scalable and secure network topologies and connectivity patterns within AWS environments. Architects the use and integration of services such as Application Load Balancers, Network Load Balancers, NAT and Internet Gateways, and VPC and S3 endpoints. 
 Leads the design and development of the company’s Infrastructure as Code frameworks, enabling consistent and automated infrastructure provisioning across environments. Architects scalable deployment patterns using Terraform and AWS CloudFormation. Establishes standards and reusable modules to ensure reliability, maintainability, and governance of cloud infrastructure; 
 Designs and maintains CI automation for continuous integration and delivery, enabling software development, testing, and deployment; 
 Leads the design and governance of the company’s end-to-end Configuration Management architecture, ensuring scalable, reliable, and auditable system configurations across all environments. Defines standards &amp; automation strategies to maintain consistency and operational excellence, mainly utilizing Ansible; 
 Architects and governs the company’s local and staging development environments, delivering a scalable, consistent developer experience across diverse hardware and operating systems. Designs flexible, multi-purpose solutions and rollout strategies to support 200+ internal users. Establishes standards, automation, and tooling to streamline setup, testing, and environment parity; 
 Leads the design of the company’s end-to-end monitoring architecture, defining how the full monitoring stack is built, deployed, and operated. Establishes standards for metrics, logs, and telemetry collection to ensure comprehensive visibility across systems and services. Designs scalable solutions that enable reliable observability and actionable insights. Ensures the monitoring platform effectively serves internal teams and drives operational excellence; 
 Leads the evaluation and introduction of new DevOps tools across the organization, ensuring the platform stack remains modern, efficient, and aligned with engineering needs. Conducts research, proof-of-concepts, and technical assessments to identify solutions that deliver the greatest operational impact. Drives adoption of tools across domains such as cloud infrastructure, CI/CD, configuration management, AWS automation, and monitoring. 

 The position requires at least 9 years of experience as a DevOps or VoIP engineer, which also includes experience with the following: 

 9 years of experience: 

 Managing and maintaining Linux-based servers, which includes any experience with tools such as SaltStack, Kubernetes, or writing in Bash; 

 5 years of experience: 

 Managing and maintaining Linux-based Web-Servers, such as Apache, Nginx, or Envoy; 
 Working with Configuration management tools at a production level, which includes any experience with Ansible or SaltStack; 
 Working with open source caching solutions tools such as Memcache; 
 Working with open source DNS tools such as bind9; 

 3 years of experience: 

 Building and maintaining complex AWS architecture

Come join the company that is reinventing cloud security and empowering businesses to thrive in the cloud. As the  fastest-growing startup ever,    Wiz is on a mission to help organizations secure cloud environments that will accelerate their businesses. Trusted by security teams all over the world, we have a proven &nbsp;  track record of success  &nbsp; and a culture that values world-class talent.&nbsp;&nbsp;  
  Our Wizards from over 20 countries work together to protect the infrastructure of our hundreds of customers, including over 50% of the Fortune 100, who trust us to scan and secure over 230 billion files daily. We’re the leading player in a massive and growing market, but it’s still early enough for you to make a significant impact. At Wiz, you’ll have the freedom to think creatively, dream big, and use your full range of skills to contribute to our record growth. Come join our team and help us create secure cloud environments that allow the best companies to move faster.&nbsp;      SUMMARY   &nbsp;  
 We’re looking for a  Cloud Security Analyst  to join our Product team and help expand the power of Wiz. In this role, you’ll play a key role in protecting our customers' cloud environments from cyber threats. Your work will directly contribute to customer success and push the boundaries of cloud security. This isn’t just a job—it’s a unique growth opportunity. You’ll gain hands-on experience that can pave the way for exciting career paths in product management, security research, or development. 
   WHAT YOU’LL DO   &nbsp;  

  Innovate and develop advanced detection mechanisms, algorithms, and automated solutions to accurately identify and classify technologies within cloud environments, enhancing Wiz's vulnerability management offering.  &nbsp;  
  Analyze cloud services, APIs, and log payloads to ensure compliance with industry standards and customer requirements.  &nbsp;  
  Stay current with the latest technologies and industry trends.  &nbsp;  
  Implement customer requests and industry standards to position Wiz as a market leader.  &nbsp;  
  Collaborate with our Research and Backend teams.  &nbsp;  

   WHAT YOU’LL BRING   &nbsp;  

  Hands-on proficiency in Linux, Windows, Python, Bash, Docker, Kubernetes, PowerShell, and a strong understanding of the OSI model.  &nbsp;  
  Solid knowledge of networking concepts and cloud infrastructure.  &nbsp;  
  Proven experience in applying cybersecurity best practices to real-world scenarios.  &nbsp;  
  Self-motivated and capable of working both independently and collaboratively within a team.  &nbsp;  
  Strong communication skills.  &nbsp;  

